  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "All of the following are contraindications of emetics except?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Corrosive ingestion"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Unconscious patient"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "CNS stimulant toxicity"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Parkinson's disease"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: D) Parkinson's disease</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<p>Emetics are used in Parkinson’s disease</p>\n\n<p>Emetics induce vomiting. There are two drugs which are used to induce vomiting:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Syrup of Ipecac</strong> (oral preparation) used in oral poisoning</li>\n\t<li><strong>Apomorphine</strong> (given as injection- I/M or S/C) used in Parkinson’s disease <strong>(Option D)</strong> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5cc2a2112e16927771874c5d97065a\">erectile</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3662597407169277718640a12868f5\">dysfunction</span> (D2 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7d8d28cda71692777180c89a3c86ce\">agonist</span> in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"32b8d1e25c1692777189a123d50ec1\">hypothalamus</span> ➞ ⬆ sexual activity)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>MECHANISM OF ACTION:</strong> Activates D2 receptors in the CTZ area.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>CONTRAINDICATIONS OF EMETICS IN <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"072b8af16e1692777196f21b086f92\">POISONING</span> :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Corrosive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"072b8af16e1692777196f21b086f92\">poisoning</span> (acids/ alkali) ➞ ⬆risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"23b5d65f051692777195987380382d\">perforation</span> <strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t<li>CNS <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bec9bb02501692777199b0f75e340e\">Stimulant</span> (cocaine/ amphetamines) ➞ ⬆risk of seizures <strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t<li>Kerosene/petroleum <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"072b8af16e1692777196f21b086f92\">poisoning</span> ➞ ⬆risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"831d67ad8a1692777182763ca62e4b\">aspiration</span> pneumonia</li>\n\t<li>Unconscious patient ➞ ⬆risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"831d67ad8a1692777182763ca62e4b\">aspiration</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1000989d33169277719652247cd559\">pneumonia</span> <strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t<li>opioid/morphine <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"072b8af16e1692777196f21b086f92\">poisoning</span> ➞ emetics are not effective</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
