    {
      "text": "A 55-year-old woman is undergoing chemotherapy for breast cancer. Despite taking her prescribed antiemetic medication, she experiences significant nausea and vomiting starting 24 hours after her chemotherapy sessions and lasting for several days. Which of the following is the 1st line drug used to relieve this patient’s chemotherapy-induced nausea and vomiting?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Ondansetron"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Dronabinol"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Fezolinetant"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Aprepitant"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: D) Aprepitant</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<p>This patient is undergoing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8602c4b260169277718439bb122cb0\">chemotherapy</span> for breast cancer, after 24 hours of therapy she complained of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9a8412e39e1692777193c550a5dbb4\">nausea</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"998fb41ebc1692777202e46891c4a7\">vomiting</span> for several days. This suggests a delayed phase in chemotherapy-induced <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9a8412e39e1692777193c550a5dbb4\">nausea</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"998fb41ebc1692777202e46891c4a7\">vomiting</span> (CINV). The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"357ecf18f2169277718661a76111ea\">DOC</span> for the same is an <strong>NK1 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9e4959f6f316927771978bb152d440\">receptor</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e432a4f3c1692777181e8e244ca0e\">antagonist</span> (e.g; Aprepitant)</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/h89giImHZ6t0ubl3ODEb1724072148.jpg\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p><br />\nPalonosetron can be used in the delayed phase by combining it with Dexamethasone. </p>\n\n<p>Fezolinetant is an NK3 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9e4959f6f316927771978bb152d440\">receptor</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e432a4f3c1692777181e8e244ca0e\">antagonist</span> used to treat <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c9ba8fa63616927771962d84263e40\">postmenopausal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bd99ec780c16927772018a45db80c2\">vasomotor</span> syndrome <strong>(Option C).</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
